    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="181"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9318.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that Chinese
                    citizens resident in Costa Rica have of late had occasion to solicit the
                    Government of the Republic of China for protection by reason of their growing
                    interests in that country. But the Government of the Republic has no diplomatic
                    or consular representative in Costa Rica.</p>
                <p>Inasmuch as the American diplomatic and consular representatives in Guatemala,
                    Nicaragua and Salvador are now looking after Chinese interests in those
                    countries, I am instructed by my Government to inquire whether similar
                    instructions can be given to the American diplomatic and consular
                    representatives in Costa Rica to use their good offices, with the consent of the
                    Costa Rican Government, in behalf of the Chinese residents in that country in
                    case of need. Such friendly action on the part of the American Government will
                    be greatly appreciated by my Government.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kai Fit Shah</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
